## Domain Architecture

```
unratified.org                          Main site — ICESCR content, advocacy, action
│
├── /educators                          Teacher-facing: curriculum, lesson plans, materials
├── /covenant                           ICESCR article-by-article guide
├── /gap                                Why the U.S. has not ratified
├── /action                             Advocacy toolkit, contact senators, templates
└── /resources                          Further reading, organizations

observatory.unratified.org              Human Rights Observatory, Hacker News Edition
│
├── /diagnosis                          Differential diagnosis (7 hypotheses)
├── /chains                             Integral chain analysis (interactive)
├── /higher-order                       Recursive higher-order effects (Orders 0-4)
├── /evidence                           Evidence matrix, data, sources
├── /landscape                          Current economic/geopolitical conditions
├── /methodology                        How the analysis works (for academics)
└── /data                               Downloadable datasets, citations, BibTeX
```

**The Observatory serves HN + Academics. The main site serves Teachers.
Cross-linking connects them at every relevant point.**

The "Hacker News Edition" subtitle signals density and intellectual honesty. It says: "We built this for people who check sources and argue about methodology." That framing earns trust with HN readers and academics simultaneously. Teachers arrive at a different door, purpose-built for their workflow.

