## Cross-Audience Flow

The three audiences don't exist in isolation. The site architecture enables organic discovery across audience boundaries:

```
                    ┌──────────────────┐
                    │   HACKER NEWS    │
                    │   SUBMISSION     │
                    └────────┬─────────┘
                             │
                             ▼
                  ┌──────────────────────┐
                  │    OBSERVATORY       │
                  │    /diagnosis        │◄──────── Academic finds
                  │                      │         via citation
                  │  Analysis engages    │
                  │  HN + Academics      │
                  └──────────┬───────────┘
                             │
              ┌──────────────┼──────────────┐
              │              │              │
              ▼              ▼              ▼
    ┌─────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐ ┌──────────────┐
    │ /covenant   │ │ /methodology │ │ /educators   │
    │             │ │              │ │              │
    │ HN reader   │ │ Academic     │ │ Teacher finds│
    │ discovers   │ │ evaluates    │ │ via search / │
    │ ICESCR      │ │ framework    │ │ colleague    │
    └──────┬──────┘ └──────┬───────┘ └──────┬───────┘
           │               │               │
           ▼               ▼               ▼
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │              /action                         │
    │  All paths converge on advocacy toolkit      │
    │                                              │
    │  HN: shares, discusses, some write senators  │
    │  Academic: cites, extends, informs policy    │
    │  Teacher: uses materials, shapes students    │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

