## Content Tailoring by Audience

The same underlying analysis gets presented differently depending on entry point:

| Content Element | HN Presentation | Teacher Presentation | Academic Presentation |
|---|---|---|---|
| Differential diagnosis | Full analysis with scoring tables | Simplified "competing explanations" activity | Full analysis + methodology appendix |
| Evidence matrix | Interactive sortable table | Worksheet with guided evaluation | Downloadable CSV + replication notes |
| ICESCR articles | Linked organically from analysis | Lesson plans per article | Cross-referenced with legal commentary |
| Higher-order effects | Full cascade visualization | "What happens next?" classroom discussion | Formal chain analysis with confidence intervals |
| Causal chains | ASCII diagrams (they love these) | Simplified flowcharts for classroom | Formal DAG notation option |
| Action items | Template letters, senator lookup | Lesson plan on civic participation | Policy brief format |
| Tagline visible | "Human Rights Observatory, Hacker News Edition" | "Classroom Resources for Human Rights Education" | "Research and Methodology" |

---

## Launch Sequencing by Audience

```
PHASE │ AUDIENCE   │ ACTION                                │ GOAL
──────┼────────────┼───────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────────
  1   │ HN         │ Submit observatory analysis to HN     │ Attention +
      │            │ Title: analysis-focused, not advocacy  │ credibility
      │            │                                        │
  2   │ Academic   │ Post methodology to SSRN / arXiv      │ Citation +
      │            │ Announce on academic social media      │ validation
      │            │                                        │
  3   │ Teacher    │ Educator outreach via networks,        │ Adoption +
      │            │ conferences, NEA/AFT channels          │ durability
      │            │                                        │
  ∞   │ All        │ Quarterly updates as landscape evolves │ Sustained
      │            │ Annual differential diagnosis refresh  │ relevance
```

**Rationale for sequencing**: HN provides the initial amplification burst. Academic engagement provides credibility that supports the educator pitch. Educator adoption creates the most durable long-term impact (shapes the judgment pipeline — the Article 13 argument in action).

